data.description:
Imagine us writing a plugin for a well-known framework which supports events' namespaces (i.e. "event1.namespace event2.namespace").

In this kata we have a predefined string representing namespace and manageEventsStrings() function with 3 signatures:

    1) manageEventsStrings(doActions, undoActions, toggleActions);
    2) manageEventsStrings(doActions, undoActions);
    3) manageEventsStrings(toggleActions).

where "doActions", "undoActions" and "toggleActions" are whitespace-separated strings.

All we need to do is:

    - remove duplicate values within each string;
    - find intersection between doAction and undoAction and if any - remove matches 
    from both strings and add this match to the toggleAction string;
    - add some predefined namespace to each event within all the strings.

"manageEventsStrings" function must return array of 3 modified strings: [doActionsWithNamespaces, undoActionsWithNamespaces, toggleActionsWithNamespaces]

The namespace variable is preloaded as:
```javascript
var namespace = "codeWars";
```
but you can define your own namespace.

Consider performance: 100 calls must run within 10ms.

Examples:
```javascript
manageEventsStrings("foo");
//returns ["", "", "foo.codeWars"]
```

```javascript
manageEventsStrings("foo", "bar");
//returns ["foo.codeWars", "bar.codeWars", ""]
```

```javascript
manageEventsStrings("open mouseenter", "close mouseleave", "toggle click");
//returns ["open.codeWars mouseenter.codeWars", 
//         "close.codeWars mouseleave.codeWars",
//         "toggle.codeWars click.codeWars"]
```

```javascript
manageEventsStrings("foo baz", "bar baz");
//returns ["foo.codeWars", "bar.codeWars", "baz.codeWars"]
```

```javascript
namespace = "myNamespace";
manageEventsStrings("open foo baz", "close bar baz", "toggle baz");
//returns ["open.myNamespace foo.myNamespace", 
//         "close.myNamespace bar.myNamespace",
//         "toggle.myNamespace baz.myNamespace"]
```
